  "texts": [
    "The data presented in Table 2 reveals that RED achieved performance comparable to other PEFT baselines across all metrics in the E2E NLG Challenge.",
    "This highlights the efficacy of fine-tuning through representation editing, not only for natural language understanding tasks but also for language generation tasks.",
    "Remarkably, RED accomplished this performance while still necessitating minimal fine-tuning of parameters.",
    "To compare RED with the most parameter-efficient variants of other PEFT methods, we set the rank of LoRA and Adapter to 1.",
    "Under these conditions, RED outperformed all such variants while still employing the fewest number of parameters (see Section 5.3 for details)."
  ],
